              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer15698827233728363457">Written in the early 1960&apos;s this book has shaped my thinking like few others. Goes a long way to explain the history of intellectual life in America, examining religion, formal education, business, and politics. If we wonder why Americans seem &quot;dumber&quot; than ever, this book offers an argument that stands up well today. One of my all-time favorites.</span>
  <span id="freeText15698827233728363457" style="display:none">Written in the early 1960's this book has shaped my thinking like few others. Goes a long way to explain the history of intellectual life in America, examining religion, formal education, business, and politics. If we wonder why Americans seem "dumber" than ever, this book offers an argument that stands up well today. One of my all-time favorites.</span>
